Kolkata vs Rajasthan Head-To-Head Match Record in Indian T20 League

Looking at the records, both the teams have evolved drastically in their strategies, players, and tactics to win the match. Till today, Kolkata Cricket Team vs Rajasthan Cricket Team have come face-to-face 25 times. Out of these 25 times, 13 were won by the Kolkata Cricket Team and 11 by Rajasthan.

Know More About Kolkata Vs Rajasthan Match

The Kolkata Cricket Team is an established team owned by Shah Rukh Khan, along with actress Juhi Chawla and her spouse Jay Mehta. Since the team is associated with the biggest superstars of the country, it gained immense popularity and debuted in the Indian T20 League in 20 08 for the first-ever time. In these ten years, the team has won the Indian T20 League 2 times in 2012 and 2014.

The high-flying Kolkata Cricket Team boasts several national and international players who excel in different areas of cricket. The team regularly practices at the iconic Eden Gardens stadium. Currently, the team is led by Shreyas Iyer, who plays for the England cricket team.

The Rajasthan Cricket Team is a popular cricket franchise founded in 2008. The team’s motto is “Halla Bol”. It was founded in 2008, the year the Indian T20 League came into existence.

Initially, the franchise of Rajasthan Cricket Team was bought jointly by Manoj Badale, Lachlan Murdoch, and RedBird Capital Partners.
Some of the best cricketers from the Rajasthan Cricket Team are Sanju Samson, Andrew Tye, Ankit Rajpoot, and others. Presently, the team is led by the team’s captain, Sanju Samson.

Tips For Picking Your Fantasy Team

Indian Fantasy League is actually virtual; however, the players are all excited to create their team through the virtual currency and start playing.

  • Before getting into the match, conduct extensive research on the possible playing 11, the weather forecast, ground conditions, pitch report, team and player statistics for that ground, and performances of the players in the previous matches.
  • Make sure that you do not build your teams by watching videos or using apps. Trust your gut instinct and create your team with your own knowledge.
  • Do not burn through your transfers at the start of the season.
  • Do not engage too much in mini-league rivalries.
  • Make sure you’re making transfers after the toss.
  • Don’t switch off the match if your team isn’t performing well.
